quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
3,30,"The Day is approaching when every soul shall find itself confronted with whatever good it has done and whatever evil it has wrought. It will then wish there is a wide space between it and the Day! Allah warns you to beware of Him; He is most tender towards His servants. {1}",footnotes:1:It is out of sheer goodwill that God warns people against deeds likelyto have devastating consequences for them.
3,31,"(O Messenger!) Tell people: 'If you indeed love Allah, follow me, and Allah will love you and will forgive you your sins. Allah is All-Forgiving, All-Compassionate.'"
3,32,"Say: 'Obey Allah and obey the Messenger.' If they turn away from this then know that Allah does not love those who refuse to obey Him and His Messenger. {1}",footnotes:1:This marks the conclusion of the first discourse. Reflection upon its contents
3,33,"Truly Allah {1} chose Adam and Noah and the descendants of Abraham and of 'Imran {2} above all mankind.",footnotes:1:'Imran was the father of Moses and Aaron
3,34,"(for His messengership) - a people alike and the seed of one another. {1} Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:The real error of the Christians lies in considering Jesus to be the son of God and a partner in His godhead
3,35,". (He also heard) when the woman of 'Imran {1} said: 'O Lord! Behold, unto You do I vow that the child in my womb is to be devoted to Your exclusive service. Accept it, then, from me. Surely You alone are All-Hearing, All-Knowing.' {2}",footnotes:1:If the 'woman of 'Imran' is interpreted as the wife of 'Imran
3,36,"But when she gave birth to a female child, she said: 'O Lord! I have given birth to a female' - and Allah knew full well what she had given birth to - 'and a female is not the same as a male. {1} I have named her Mary and commit her and her offspring to You for protection from Satan, the accursed.'",footnotes:1:Since a boy is free from some of the physical shortcomings and social disabilities associated with a girl
3,37,"Thereupon her Lord graciously accepted Mary and vouchsafed to her a goodly growth and placed her in the care of Zechariah. Whenever Zechariah {1} visited her in the sanctuary, {2} he found her provided with food. He asked her: 'O Mary, how did this come to you?' She said: 'It is from Allah. Allah provides sustenance to whom He wills beyond all reckoning.'",footnotes:1:The word mihrab usually refers to that niche in mosques where the leader of the prayer stands. In this instance
